# Simple Deployment

This repo contains a simple Sinatra application.

Write configuration code that deploys this application onto a vanilla OS image.

## Parameters

- Use a vanilla image, e.g. Centos/Fedora/Ubuntu/Debian/RHEL
- Use a web/application server of your choosing
- Serve up the application on port 80
- Ensure that the server is locked down and secure
- Actually deploy the application

## Deliverables

- Chef/Puppet/Ansible/Babushka/Shell scripts that we can use to deploy the application.

## Local

```
git clone git://github.com/tnh/simple-sinatra-app.git
shell $ bundle install
shell $ bundle exec rackup
```

